    "summary": "With over twenty-five years\u2019 experience as a (group) controller in the area of finance and controlling, I am available as an interim manager to help you in realizing your goals.\n\nAfter Business Economics at the Erasmus University in Rotterdam, my built my experience in the telecom industry, machine industry and manufacturing industry, often for European subsidiaries of US based corporations or companies who just had been taken over by US based shareholders and were in need of full implementation of US GAAP and SoX.\n\nI favor projects where my responsibility go beyond consultancy (telling you what you need to do), to actually getting the things done myself. My assignments in the last couple of years have been in the area of clear and measurable deliverables in the form of implementation of SoX, implementation of Hyperion, end responsibility for EMEA annual accounts, implementing VAT control structures, managing EU VAT projects and improving accounting and controlling in the EMEA area for various companies.\n\nMy objective is to get the job done, in a manner that after the end of the assignment, the existing organization is able to take over full responsibilities. I favor informal organizations where we work  together to jointly achieve the goals and leave the company with a sustainable and future proof solution.\n\nFields of experience: EU VAT & CIT, Controlling, Accounting, Audit, IFRS, Dutch GAAP, US GAAP, IFRS, Hyperion, implementing ERP and CRM , SAP R/3 FI CO PS MM Admin, Exact, Business planning, business modelling, procedures, intercompany pricing, tax, cost analysis, forecasting, investments analysis, due diligences, revenue recognition",
